begin_memory_text: We asked each other where we were from. He was from the south eastern part of Ohio. He said he paid $80,000 for a nice big house and I told him I paid $50,000 for a studio apartment.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the weather in our respective states. He said it gets below 0 degrees where he's at and that after he remodeled his garage, it was still very cold. He said his garage was a place for his kids to hang out.
end_memory_text: We talked about the survey sites like mturk. He said he was banned from mturk to which I replied that I was as well. We theorized that it was due to inactivity on the site. We also agreed that it wasn't worth the effort.
rest_of_day_open: I'm finally feeling better as far as back pain and nausea is concerned. I'm going to go on a run later, for sure this time. I'll likely go work for a little bit as well. I'd also like to look into opportunities related to going back to school to get a degree.
critical_positive: What worked is that we both liked drinking beer and seemed to have a similar sense of humor. We both were working adults who owned property and agreed on the fact that taxation is theft. We also agreed on the fact that the city is not the best place to live.
critical_negative: What didn't work so well was that we seemed to be in different stages of our lives. He was more successful in the fact that he has a more reliable job and likely a degree as well. He also had a few kids which I don't have and that made it harder to relate.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were from. He was in Virginia and I was telling him about living in Ohio. He told me he had family near where I live. We talked about how long we've been using Prolific and what jobs we do briefly.
middle_memory_text: We talked about jobs and housing. He was telling me about a shooting that happened outside his apartment/condo and I told him that we have people shooting all the time here but mostly hunters. We talked about the pandemic and about how it has effected each of us.
end_memory_text: We talked about other small income opportunities and sites we had used. We also talked about how a lot of them aren't worth it. We are both are banned from mturk, probably from leaving accounts dormant too long, but it seems like a scam and we agreed on that.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week will be busy but I'm very excited for it. We have baseball games nearly every day for the next week but they are enjoyable and I love watching them. I do have a lot of work to do but the majority of the work I took on this week has gone well.
critical_positive: I think in general the conversation went well. We talked a lot about doing these smaller "beer money" type jobs and it worked into having bigger conversations about beer, breweries, music, and so forth. The natural flow was better than normal, which made me think that it went better than I expected.
critical_negative: I think there wasn't specifically anything that didn't work well. We both seemed to have a good conversation. At most, I would say that we both kind of talked over each other a little bit here and there, or I talked way too much, but that wasn't necessarily fatal to the whole conversation.
